          <div class="container">
             <h1 class="h2 page-title">Disable Criteo services on Internet browsers</h1>          </div>
       </div>
        <div id="basic-page" class="layout-mode-privacy-2019 bg--light-smoke py-5 pb-lg-6">
                    <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                                            <div class="col-sm-12 col-lg-4 col-xl-3">
                            <div id="basic-page-sidebar-left">
                                <div id="table-of-contents">
                                    <h2 class="toc-heading">
                                       Table of Contents                                    </h2>
                                    <ul id="top-list">
                                        <li><a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a></li><li class="current-page">Disable Criteo services on Internet browsers</li><li><a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-mobile-applications/">Disable Criteo services on mobile applications</a></li><li><a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/how-we-use-your-data/">How we use your data</a></li><li><a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/how-criteo-services-work-across-environments/">How Criteo services work across environments</a></li><li><a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/your-rights/">Your rights</a></li><li><a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/our-partners/">Our partners</a></li><li><a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/ccpa-privacy-policy/">CCPA Privacy Policy</a></li>                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div><!-- /#basic-page-sidebar-right -->
                        </div><!-- /.col -->
                                            
                    <div class="col-sm-12 col-lg-8 col-xl-9">
                        <div id="basic-page-content">
                            <p><div class="notios hidden">
You have been detected as using an Internet browser and the information below regarding how to disable Criteo services has been personalized accordingly.</p>
<p>Click <a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-mobile-applications/">here</a> if you want to know how to disable Criteo services on mobile application.<br />

    </div><br />
<div class="ios-only hidden">
<br />
You have been detected as browsing with Safari iOS v11.0 and higher and the information below regarding how to disable Criteo services has been personalized accordingly.<br />
Click <a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-mobile-applications/">here</a> if you want to know how to disable Criteo services on mobile application.<br />

    </div><br />
<div class="optout-wysiwyg "  style="display:none;">
        <div class="title p-3"> Status of Criteo services</div>
        <div id="loader" class=" p-3"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.criteo.com/wp-content/themes/criteo2017/img/loader.gif"/> </div>
        <span class="optout-services-enabled p-3">Criteo services enabled on the browser you are currently using</span>
        <span class="optout-services-disabled  p-3 ">Criteo services disabled on the browser you are currently using</span>
        <span class="optout-services-safari  p-3 ">Default settings of the browser you are currently using limit the use of third-party cookies as well as our capability to easily know if you have decided to disable Criteo Services. To make sure that Criteo services are disabled in the browser you are currently using, please click on the button below.</span>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/promise-polyfill@8/dist/polyfill.min.js"></script>

<script src="/wp-content/themes/criteo2017/js/optout-new-2019.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
    </div><br />
<div class="modal fade" id="success" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg pt-4" role="document">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header" style="text-align: right;background:#c2c2c2 ">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body modal-center" style="background:white">You have successfully disabled Criteo services.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    </div><br />
<div class="notios hidden">
</p>
<h4>Your data, your choice</h4>
<p>To withdraw your consent to all Criteo services simply click on the button below:<br />

  <div id="loader" class="button-loader-btn" style="display:none"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.criteo.com/wp-content/themes/criteo2017/img/loader.gif"/> </div>
<div class="optout-button" style="display:;">
       <a id="" class="opt-out opt-out-2019" ><button class="button button__orange-bg"><span>Disable Criteo services</span></button></a>
    </div></p>
<h4>What will change?</h4>
<p>Disable Criteo services will result in:</p>
<ul>
<li>The deletion of the cookies dropped by Criteo in your browser you are currently using that allows us:
<ul>
<li>to recognize your browser or device;</li>
<li>and to link to you the data we have at our disposal.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>The termination of the collection of your personal data for processing activities based on your consent.</li>
<li>The termination of the display of ads by Criteo, based on your consent, on the browser you are currently using.</li>
</ul>
<p>Please note that Criteo can continue to process your personal data collected before you disabled Criteo services on the basis of Criteo’s legitimate interest.<br />
To learn more about the personal data processed by Criteo go to <a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/how-we-use-your-data/">How we use your data</a>. To exercise your other rights, go to <a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/your-rights/">Understand my rights</a>.</p>
<p><div class="lightbulb">
        <div class="content p-3 ">Please note that disabling Criteo services does not prevent ads from being displayed by other industry players. If you want to quickly and easily withdraw your consent to interest-based advertising from a range of industry players, including Criteo, we invite you to use the platforms provided by the following self-regulatory organizations:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://thenai.org/" rel="nofollow">Network Advertising Initiative&#8217;s platform</a> and/or <a class="external-link" href="http://www.aboutads.info/consumers" rel="nofollow">Digital Advertising Alliance&#8217;s platform</a> if you live in US.</li>
<li>Criteo may use hashed e-mails to provide tailored advertising by combining a hashed e-mail with another identifier. If you do not want your information linked to your hashed e-mail address, you may opt out through the <a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/optout/email">Network Advertising Initiative’s Audience-Matched Opt-Out Tool</a>.</li>
<li>IAB Europe&#8217;s platform (<a class="external-link" href="http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" rel="nofollow">YourOnlinechoices</a>) if you live within the EU.</div>
    </div></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>If you wish to extend your choice to other browsers or to other devices, we invite you to repeat the operation from each of them. To facilitate this operation, you can:</p>
<ul>
<li>Copy the following URL and paste it into another browser to extend your choice to it: <a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/">https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/</a></li>
<li>Or flash the following QR code with a device and open the link to which it refers with another browser to extend your choice to it:<br />
<img decoding="async" style="max-width:90%;" src="https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?chs=300x300&cht=qr&chl=https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/"></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>When it will change?</h4>
<p>Criteo will stop displaying ads as soon as possible and at the latest after a maximum period of 24 hours.</p>
<p>Please note that it may take up to five weeks to process your request on Facebook as it is a separate environment over which we have no control. If you wish to immediately stop displaying our ads on your Facebook account, we invite you to modify the settings by clicking here: <a class="external-link" href="https://www.facebook.com/settings/?tab=ads" rel="nofollow">Facebook settings</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Is the change permanent?</h4>
<p>Your choice will be saved in a dedicated cookie stored in your browser. This allows us to ensure the technical preservation of your choice by minimizing the impact on your privacy since no information will be stored in our systems on this subject. If you delete this cookie or update your device&#8217;s operating system, we may no longer be able to remember your choice. In which case, we invite you to simply repeat the operation.</p>
<p>Please also note that some mobile applications may use or rely on a technical feature called “webview” that allows app developer’s to display web applications or web pages directly in their application without leaving the application to open your usual browser. A webview can be independent both of your usual browser and the mobile application environment. Therefore we would recommend to withdraw consent also for this specific environment if you do not want to be served with Criteo advertisements.</p>
<p>
    </div><br />
<div class="ios-only hidden">
</p>
<h4>Your data, your choice</h4>
<p>Please note that the settings of your Safari browser may limit our technical ability to allow you to withdraw your consent to Criteo services, exercise your right to be forgotten and your right to object to the processing that Criteo may make of your personal data. Criteo offers several alternatives to you in order to provide you with the same control tools as those we provide to the users of other browsers. Opting out on other browsers only takes one click.</p>
<div class="accordion-wysiwyg ">
    <div class="title p-3 pl-5"><i class="arrow p-3 fas fa-chevron-right"></i>ALTERNATIVE N°1: Change settings and disable Criteo</div>
    <div class="inner p-3">
    <div class="content pl-3">
<p>1.Change browser settings for Criteo to be able to know and respect your choice on all websites.</p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>Open Settings app</li>
<li>Select Safari</li>
<li>Switch Off “Prevent Cross-Site Tracking”</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>2. Come back to this page after changing your settings.</p>
<p>3. Disable Criteo services here.<br />

  <div id="loader" class="button-loader-btn" style="display:none"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.criteo.com/wp-content/themes/criteo2017/img/loader.gif"/> </div>
<div class="optout-button" style="display:;">
       <a id="" class="opt-out opt-out-2019" ><button class="button button__orange-bg"><span>Disable Criteo services</span></button></a>
    </div></p>
<p>4. Force Safari App to close</p>
<div class="lightbulb">
        <div class="content p-3 ">If you need instructions on how to force an app to close, you can read more on: <a class="external-link" href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT201330" rel="nofollow">Apple Support&#8217;s instructions </a></div>
    </div>
<h4>What will change?</h4>
<p>Such a configuration of your smartphone will result in:</p>
<ul>
<li>The deletion of the identifier stored in the browser you are currently using that allows us:
<ul>
<li>to recognize your browser or device;</li>
<li>and to link to you the data we have at our disposal.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>The termination of the collection of your personal data.</li>
<li>And the termination of the display of ads by Criteo on the browser you are currently using.</li>
</ul>
<p><div class="lightbulb">
        <div class="content p-3 ">Please note it does not prevent ads from being displayed by other industry players. If you want to quickly and easily withdraw your consent to interest-based advertising from a range of industry players, including Criteo, we invite you to use the platforms provided by the following self-regulatory organizations:</p>
<ul>
<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.networkadvertising.org/index.asp" rel="nofollow">Network Advertising Initiative&#8217;s platform</a> and/or <a class="external-link" href="http://www.aboutads.info/consumers" rel="nofollow">Digital Advertising Alliance&#8217;s platform</a> if you live in US.</li>
<li>Criteo may use hashed e-mails to provide tailored advertising by combining a hashed e-mail with another identifier. If you do not want your information linked to your hashed e-mail address, you may opt out through the <a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/optout/email">Network Advertising Initiative’s Audience-Matched Opt-Out Tool</a>.</li>
<li>IAB Europe&#8217;s platform (<a class="external-link" href="http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" rel="nofollow">YourOnlinechoices</a>) if you live within the EU.</div>
    </div></li>
</ul>
<p>If you wish to extend your choice to other browsers installed on this device or to other devices, we invite you to repeat the operation from each of them. To facilitate this operation, you can:</p>
<ul>
<li>Copy the following URL and paste it into another browser to extend your choice to it: <a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/">https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/</a></li>
<li>Or flash the following QR code with a device and open the link to which it refers with another browser to extend your choice to it:<br />
<img decoding="async" style="max-width:90%;" src="https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?chs=300x300&cht=qr&chl=https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/"></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>When it will change?</h4>
<p>Criteo will stop displaying ads as soon as possible and at the latest after a maximum period of 24 hours.</p>
<p>Please note that it may take up to five weeks to process your request on Facebook as it is a separate environment over which we have no control. If you wish to immediately stop displaying our ads on your Facebook account, we invite you to modify the settings by clicking here:  <a class="external-link" href="https://www.facebook.com/settings/?tab=ads" rel="nofollow">Facebook settings</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Is the change permanent?</h4>
<p>Your choice will be saved in a dedicated cookie stored in your browser. This allows us to ensure the technical preservation of your choice by minimizing the impact on your privacy since no information will be stored in our systems on this subject. If you delete this cookie or update your device&#8217;s operating system, we may no longer be able to remember your choice. In which case, we invite you to simply repeat the operation.</p>
<p></div>
    </div>
    </div><br />
<div class="accordion-wysiwyg ">
    <div class="title p-3 pl-5"><i class="arrow p-3 fas fa-chevron-right"></i>ALTERNATIVE N°2: Install a content-blocking app to block personalized advertising from Criteo and others</div>
    <div class="inner p-3">
    <div class="content pl-3"></p>
<ol>
<li>Download <a href="https://apps.apple.com/fr/app/disconnect-free-tracker-protection-for-safari/id1049073550">Disconnect.me</a></li>
<li>Change browser settings</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li style="list-style: none;">
<ul>
<li>Open Settings app</li>
<li>Select Safari</li>
<li>Select “Content Blockers”</li>
<li>Switch On “Privacy”</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>What will change?</h4>
<p>Such a configuration of your smartphone will result in:</p>
<ul>
<li>The termination of the collection of your personal data.</li>
<li>And the termination of the display of ads by Criteo when you are browsing from your web browser installed on the smartphone you are using.</li>
</ul>
<div class="lightbulb">
        <div class="content p-3 ">Please note it might not prevent ads from being displayed by other industry players.</div>
    </div>
<p>If you wish to extend your choice to other browsers installed on this device or to other devices, we invite you to repeat the operation from each of them. To facilitate this operation, you can:</p>
<ul>
<li>Copy the following URL and paste it into another browser to extend your choice to it: <a href="https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/">https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/</a></li>
<li>Or flash the following QR code with a device and open the link to which it refers with another browser to extend your choice to it:<br />
<img decoding="async" style="max-width:90%;" src="https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?chs=300x300&cht=qr&chl=https://www.criteo.com/privacy/disable-criteo-services-on-internet-browsers/"></li>
</ul>
<h4>When it will change?</h4>
<p>Criteo will stop displaying ads as soon as possible and at the latest after a maximum period of 24 hours.</p>
<p>Please note that it may take up to five weeks to process your request on Facebook as it is a separate environment over which we have no control. If you wish to immediately stop displaying our ads on your Facebook account, we invite you to modify the settings by clicking here:  <a class="external-link" href="https://www.facebook.com/settings/?tab=ads" rel="nofollow">Facebook settings</a>.</p>
<h4></h4>
<h4>Is the change permanent?</h4>
<p class="auto-cursor-target" style="margin: 0in; margin-bottom: .0001pt;">If you modify the settings of your device, or if you update your device&#8217;s operating system, we may no longer be able to remember your choice. In which case, we invite you to simply repeat the operation.</p>
<p></div>
    </div>
    </div></p>
<p>Please also note that some mobile applications may use or rely on a technical feature called “webview” that allows app developer’s to display web applications or web pages directly in their application without leaving the application to open your usual browser. A webview can be independent both of your usual browser and the mobile application environment. Therefore we would recommend to opt out also from this specific environment if you do not want to be served with Criteo advertisements.</p>
<p>
    </div></p>
